Package ohos.aafwk.ability

Interface AbilityForm.OnAcquiredCallback

  • Enclosing class:
    AbilityForm

    public static interface AbilityForm.OnAcquiredCallback
    Provides callback methods that are invoked when an AbilityForm instance created by the supplier is obtained or destroyed on the client.

    This interface provides callback methods that are called after an asynchronous request sent by calling AbilitySlice#acquireAbilityFormAsync(Intent, OnAcquiredCallback) on the client. The callback methods are used to notify the client that the AbilityForm request has been processed.

    Since:
    1

    • Method Detail

      • onAcquired

        void onAcquired​(AbilityForm abilityForm)
        Called when an AbilityForm instance created by the supplier is obtained on the client.

        This method is called back when:

        • The asynchronous request sent from the client by calling AbilitySlice#acquireAbilityFormAsync(Intent, OnAcquiredCallback) has been processed.
        • The supplier is restarted by the Ability Manager Service.

        Parameters:
        abilityForm - Indicates the AbilityForm instance created by the supplier by calling Ability#onCreateForm().
        Since:
        1

      • onDestroyed

        void onDestroyed​(AbilityForm abilityForm)
        Called when an AbilityForm has been destroyed.

        You will be notified through this callback method when an AbilityForm is destroyed. You can also use this method to reconnect to the AbilityForm or clear resources.

        Parameters:
        abilityForm - Indicates the destroyed AbilityForm.
        Since:
        1
